                            <comment id="17429345" author="xmarker" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:33:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I investigate the issue related code and i think the issue may be occur with flowing scene:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.When call `retrievalEventHandler.waitForNewLeader(timeout)` at line 434, in&#160;TestingRetrievalBase.waitForNewLeader wait a correct leader information&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. But&#160;when return `leader.getLeaderAddress()` in&#160;TestingRetrievalBase the&#160;leaderRetrievalDriver was notified a empty leader information(may be zookeeper connection suspend or lost, see ZooKeeperLeaderRetrievalDriver.handleStateChange)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. So we can use a local variable to store leaderEventQueue.poll &apos;s result in case the object field variable change .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=wangyang0918&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;wangyang0918&quot;&gt;wangyang0918&lt;/a&gt;&#160; &#160;do you have any good advice ?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
